cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the behavior of stack-augmented recurrent neural network (RNN) models and their ability to solve tasks related to pushdown transducers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the training difficulties of stack RNNs, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of neural networks to solve tasks related to pushdown transducers also makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also deals with the behavior of RNNs, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of stacks as unstructured memory, which makes cs.SD (Sound) a possible category as well.
